notes: Title, date and keywords based on information provided by the photographer.

Little Free Libraries, now found in thousands of American neighborhoods, are book repositories where anyone and everyone is invited to leave a book, or take one without charge. Befitting the neighborhood, the monster, created by Hirotsune Tashima and Jason Butler, is reading a poem entitled, "The End of the Chapter" by Paul Laurence Dunbar.

LC Land ownership maps, 6 Available also through the Library of Congress Web site as a raster image. AACR2
